{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867552011,"sessionID":"ses_2860db1f3ffeYXb6GNuqH407Xv","part":{"id":"prt_d79f36dea0018Qwz1IB5qKTIK2","messageID":"msg_d79f3577e001VS8h9OZ75jJLTp","sessionID":"ses_2860db1f3ffeYXb6GNuqH407Xv","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_a130a67e650043a9bdc11433","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","newString":"# Delta Spec: AR-027 ŌĆö SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `CodeInterpreterClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute code/files via the Router (data plane).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-027\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK requires a `CodeInterpreterClient` class that allows users to:\n1. Create and manage Code Interpreter sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)\n2. Execute commands, run code, and manage files through the Router (data plane)\n3. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-027-001: CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-001-A ŌĆö Context manager cleanup\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-001-B ŌĆö Data plane init failure after session create\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-001-C ŌĆö Router URL required\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-001-D ŌĆö Constructor parameters with defaults\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n- **WHEN** the constructor runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL set `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-001-E ŌĆö Reuse existing session_id\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with an existing `session_id`\n- **WHEN** initialization runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL skip session creation and use the provided session_id directly for data plane initialization\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-002: Code Interpreter operations ŌĆö execute, files, stop\n\nThe system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-A ŌĆö Command non-zero exit\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n- **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-B ŌĆö Python code execution path\n- **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n- **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-C ŌĆö Write file operation\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(content, remote_path)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request succeeds\n- **THEN** the file SHALL be created at the specified remote path with content base64 encoded and mode `0644`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-D ŌĆö Upload file operation\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` is called\n- **WHEN** the file exists locally\n- **THEN** the file SHALL be uploaded as multipart form data to `api/files` with the session header\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-E ŌĆö Download file operation\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` is called\n- **WHEN** the remote file exists\n- **THEN** the file SHALL be downloaded as a stream and written to the local path\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-F ŌĆö List files operation\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\".\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request succeeds\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the listing from `api/files` with query parameter `path`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-G ŌĆö Stop operation\n- **GIVEN** `stop()` is called\n- **WHEN** the client has an active session\n- **THEN** the data plane session SHALL be closed and the control plane session SHALL be deleted\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-003: HTTP client contracts ŌĆö control plane\n\nThe system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-003-A ŌĆö Create session\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n- **WHEN** the request succeeds\n- **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-003-B ŌĆö Delete session\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n- **WHEN** the server returns 404\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-003-C ŌĆö Workload Manager URL and auth\n- **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-004: HTTP client contracts ŌĆö data plane (Code Interpreter)\n\nThe system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-004-A ŌĆö Data plane base URL construction\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with `router_url`, `namespace`, and `cr_name`\n- **WHEN** `base_url` is not provided\n- **THEN** the base URL SHALL be constructed as `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-004-B ŌĆö Execute command\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n- **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-004-C ŌĆö Write file via data plane\n- **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-004-D ŌĆö Upload file via data plane\n- **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-004-E ŌĆö Download file via data plane\n- **WHEN** `download_file` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL `GET api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True` where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-004-F ŌĆö List files via data plane\n- **WHEN** `list_files` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL `GET api/files` with query parameter `path`\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-005: Session header management\n\nThe system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-005-A ŌĆö Code Interpreter session header\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n- **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n- **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-006: Exception hierarchy\n\nThe system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-006-A ŌĆö Command failure\n- **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-006-B ŌĆö Session error definition\n- **GIVEN** `SessionError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n- **WHEN** a session operation fails\n- **THEN** `SessionError` MAY be raised by the client\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-006-C ŌĆö Data plane error definition\n- **GIVEN** `DataPlaneError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n- **WHEN** a data plane operation fails\n- **THEN** `DataPlaneError` MAY be raised by the client\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-007: Timeout behavior\n\nThe system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-007-A ŌĆö Per-call override for code execution\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n- **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n- **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-007-B ŌĆö Connection pool configuration\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` or `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n- **WHEN** no pool settings are provided\n- **THEN** the defaults SHALL be `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-008: Public API surface\n\nThe system SHALL export the `CodeInterpreterClient` from the root package.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-008-A ŌĆö Root package exports\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/__init__.py` is imported\n- **WHEN** `__all__` is accessed\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-008-B ŌĆö Clients submodule exports\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` is imported\n- **WHEN** `__all__` is accessed\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `[\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: CodeInterpreterClient constructs with proper defaults (name, namespace, ttl, verbose)\n- [ ] AC002: CodeInterpreterClient creates session via ControlPlaneClient when session_id not provided\n- [ ] AC003: CodeInterpreterClient supports context manager protocol with proper cleanup\n- [ ] AC004: CodeInterpreterClient handles data plane init failure with session cleanup\n- [ ] AC005: CodeInterpreterClient raises ValueError when router_url is missing\n- [ ] AC006: execute_command raises CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit code\n- [ ] AC007: run_code supports python/py/python3 languages with timestamped file execution\n- [ ] AC008: write_file creates remote files with base64 content and mode 0644\n- [ ] AC009: upload_file uploads files via multipart to data plane\n- [ ] AC010: download_file downloads files as streams to local path\n- [ ] AC011: list_files returns file listing from data plane\n- [ ] AC012: stop closes data plane and deletes control plane session\n- [ ] AC013: ControlPlaneClient.create_session returns sessionId from response\n- [ ] AC014: ControlPlaneClient.delete_session returns True on 404\n- [ ] AC015: ControlPlaneClient resolves base_url and auth from env/args\n- [ ] AC016: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components\n- [ ] AC017: Session header x-agentcube-session-id is set on all data plane requests\n- [ ] AC018: Exception hierarchy includes AgentCubeError, CommandExecutionError, SessionError, DataPlaneError\n- [ ] AC019: Default timeouts are 120s read, 5.0s connect\n- [ ] AC020: Connection pool defaults are 10 connections, 10 max size\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Package Layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | Main client for Code Interpreter sessions |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | Handles Workload Manager API calls |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Handles Router data plane API calls |\n| `AgentCubeError` | Base exception class |\n| `CommandExecutionError` | Raised on command non-zero exit |\n| `SessionError` | Raised on session operations failure |\n| `DataPlaneError` | Raised on data plane operations failure |\n\n### Configuration Resolution\n\n| Component | Resolved settings |\n|-----------|-------------------|\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ŌåÉ `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ŌåÉ `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ŌåÉ arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient` |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Base design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Base spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- Package root: `agentcube/`\n- Source location: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`","oldString":"# Delta Spec: AR-027 ŌĆö SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Overview\n\n<!-- Brief description of what this spec covers -->\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-027\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: <!-- Reference to base spec(s), e.g., sdk-python/spec.md -->\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\n<!-- Context and motivation for this change -->\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: <!-- Feature name -->\n\nThe system SHALL <!-- description -->\n\n#### Scenario: <!-- Scenario name -->\n- **GIVEN** <!-- precondition -->\n- **WHEN** <!-- trigger -->\n- **THEN** <!-- expected outcome -->\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. <!-- First acceptance criterion -->\n2. <!-- Second acceptance criterion -->\n3. <!-- Additional criteria as needed -->\n\n---\n\n**End of Delta Spec AR-027**"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md\n@@ -1,44 +1,284 @@\n # Delta Spec: AR-027 ŌĆö SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n \n ## Overview\n \n-<!-- Brief description of what this spec covers -->\n+This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `CodeInterpreterClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute code/files via the Router (data plane).\n \n ## Base Specifications\n \n - **AR**: AR-027\n - **Module**: `sdk-python`\n - **Language**: Python\n - **Size**: M\n-- **Base Specs**: <!-- Reference to base spec(s), e.g., sdk-python/spec.md -->\n+- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n \n ---\n \n ## Background\n \n-<!-- Context and motivation for this change -->\n+The AgentCube Python SDK requires a `CodeInterpreterClient` class that allows users to:\n+1. Create and manage Code Interpreter sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)\n+2. Execute commands, run code, and manage files through the Router (data plane)\n+3. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n \n ---\n \n ## Requirements\n \n-### Requirement: <!-- Feature name -->\n+### AR-027-001: CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle\n \n-The system SHALL <!-- description -->\n+The system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n \n-#### Scenario: <!-- Scenario name -->\n-- **GIVEN** <!-- precondition -->\n-- **WHEN** <!-- trigger -->\n-- **THEN** <!-- expected outcome -->\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-001-A ŌĆö Context manager cleanup\n+- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n+- **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n+- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n \n+#### Scenario: AR-027-001-B ŌĆö Data plane init failure after session create\n+- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n+- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n+- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-001-C ŌĆö Router URL required\n+- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n+- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n+- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-001-D ŌĆö Constructor parameters with defaults\n+- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n+- **WHEN** the constructor runs\n+- **THEN** it SHALL set `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-001-E ŌĆö Reuse existing session_id\n+- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with an existing `session_id`\n+- **WHEN** initialization runs\n+- **THEN** it SHALL skip session creation and use the provided session_id directly for data plane initialization\n+\n ---\n \n+### AR-027-002: Code Interpreter operations ŌĆö execute, files, stop\n+\n+The system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-002-A ŌĆö Command non-zero exit\n+- **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n+- **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-002-B ŌĆö Python code execution path\n+- **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n+- **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-002-C ŌĆö Write file operation\n+- **GIVEN** `write_file(content, remote_path)` is called\n+- **WHEN** the request succeeds\n+- **THEN** the file SHALL be created at the specified remote path with content base64 encoded and mode `0644`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-002-D ŌĆö Upload file operation\n+- **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` is called\n+- **WHEN** the file exists locally\n+- **THEN** the file SHALL be uploaded as multipart form data to `api/files` with the session header\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-002-E ŌĆö Download file operation\n+- **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` is called\n+- **WHEN** the remote file exists\n+- **THEN** the file SHALL be downloaded as a stream and written to the local path\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-002-F ŌĆö List files operation\n+- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\".\")` is called\n+- **WHEN** the request succeeds\n+- **THEN** the system SHALL return the listing from `api/files` with query parameter `path`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-002-G ŌĆö Stop operation\n+- **GIVEN** `stop()` is called\n+- **WHEN** the client has an active session\n+- **THEN** the data plane session SHALL be closed and the control plane session SHALL be deleted\n+\n+---\n+\n+### AR-027-003: HTTP client contracts ŌĆö control plane\n+\n+The system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-003-A ŌĆö Create session\n+- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n+- **WHEN** the request succeeds\n+- **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-003-B ŌĆö Delete session\n+- **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n+- **WHEN** the server returns 404\n+- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-003-C ŌĆö Workload Manager URL and auth\n+- **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n+- **WHEN** the client initializes\n+- **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n+\n+---\n+\n+### AR-027-004: HTTP client contracts ŌĆö data plane (Code Interpreter)\n+\n+The system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-004-A ŌĆö Data plane base URL construction\n+- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with `router_url`, `namespace`, and `cr_name`\n+- **WHEN** `base_url` is not provided\n+- **THEN** the base URL SHALL be constructed as `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-004-B ŌĆö Execute command\n+- **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n+- **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-004-C ŌĆö Write file via data plane\n+- **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n+- **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-004-D ŌĆö Upload file via data plane\n+- **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n+- **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-004-E ŌĆö Download file via data plane\n+- **WHEN** `download_file` runs\n+- **THEN** it SHALL `GET api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True` where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-004-F ŌĆö List files via data plane\n+- **WHEN** `list_files` runs\n+- **THEN** it SHALL `GET api/files` with query parameter `path`\n+\n+---\n+\n+### AR-027-005: Session header management\n+\n+The system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests.\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-005-A ŌĆö Code Interpreter session header\n+- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n+- **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n+- **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n+\n+---\n+\n+### AR-027-006: Exception hierarchy\n+\n+The system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-006-A ŌĆö Command failure\n+- **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n+- **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n+- **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-006-B ŌĆö Session error definition\n+- **GIVEN** `SessionError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n+- **WHEN** a session operation fails\n+- **THEN** `SessionError` MAY be raised by the client\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-006-C ŌĆö Data plane error definition\n+- **GIVEN** `DataPlaneError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n+- **WHEN** a data plane operation fails\n+- **THEN** `DataPlaneError` MAY be raised by the client\n+\n+---\n+\n+### AR-027-007: Timeout behavior\n+\n+The system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-007-A ŌĆö Per-call override for code execution\n+- **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n+- **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n+- **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-007-B ŌĆö Connection pool configuration\n+- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` or `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n+- **WHEN** no pool settings are provided\n+- **THEN** the defaults SHALL be `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n+\n+---\n+\n+### AR-027-008: Public API surface\n+\n+The system SHALL export the `CodeInterpreterClient` from the root package.\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-008-A ŌĆö Root package exports\n+- **GIVEN** `agentcube/__init__.py` is imported\n+- **WHEN** `__all__` is accessed\n+- **THEN** it SHALL contain `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n+\n+#### Scenario: AR-027-008-B ŌĆö Clients submodule exports\n+- **GIVEN** `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` is imported\n+- **WHEN** `__all__` is accessed\n+- **THEN** it SHALL contain `[\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n+\n+---\n+\n ## Acceptance Criteria\n \n-1. <!-- First acceptance criterion -->\n-2. <!-- Second acceptance criterion -->\n-3. <!-- Additional criteria as needed -->\n+- [ ] AC001: CodeInterpreterClient constructs with proper defaults (name, namespace, ttl, verbose)\n+- [ ] AC002: CodeInterpreterClient creates session via ControlPlaneClient when session_id not provided\n+- [ ] AC003: CodeInterpreterClient supports context manager protocol with proper cleanup\n+- [ ] AC004: CodeInterpreterClient handles data plane init failure with session cleanup\n+- [ ] AC005: CodeInterpreterClient raises ValueError when router_url is missing\n+- [ ] AC006: execute_command raises CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit code\n+- [ ] AC007: run_code supports python/py/python3 languages with timestamped file execution\n+- [ ] AC008: write_file creates remote files with base64 content and mode 0644\n+- [ ] AC009: upload_file uploads files via multipart to data plane\n+- [ ] AC010: download_file downloads files as streams to local path\n+- [ ] AC011: list_files returns file listing from data plane\n+- [ ] AC012: stop closes data plane and deletes control plane session\n+- [ ] AC013: ControlPlaneClient.create_session returns sessionId from response\n+- [ ] AC014: ControlPlaneClient.delete_session returns True on 404\n+- [ ] AC015: ControlPlaneClient resolves base_url and auth from env/args\n+- [ ] AC016: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components\n+- [ ] AC017: Session header x-agentcube-session-id is set on all data plane requests\n+- [ ] AC018: Exception hierarchy includes AgentCubeError, CommandExecutionError, SessionError, DataPlaneError\n+- [ ] AC019: Default timeouts are 120s read, 5.0s connect\n+- [ ] AC020: Connection pool defaults are 10 connections, 10 max size\n \n ---\n \n-**End of Delta Spec AR-027**\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+## Architecture Notes\n+\n+### Package Layout\n+\n+| Path | Role |\n+|------|------|\n+| `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n+| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n+| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n+| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n+| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n+| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n+| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n+| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n+| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n+\n+### Key Components\n+\n+| Component | Description |\n+|-----------|-------------|\n+| `CodeInterpreterClient` | Main client for Code Interpreter sessions |\n+| `ControlPlaneClient` | Handles Workload Manager API calls |\n+| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Handles Router data plane API calls |\n+| `AgentCubeError` | Base exception class |\n+| `CommandExecutionError` | Raised on command non-zero exit |\n+| `SessionError` | Raised on session operations failure |\n+| `DataPlaneError` | Raised on data plane operations failure |\n+\n+### Configuration Resolution\n+\n+| Component | Resolved settings |\n+|-----------|-------------------|\n+| `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ŌåÉ `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ŌåÉ `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n+| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ŌåÉ arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient` |\n+| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n+\n+---\n+\n+## References\n+\n+- Base design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n+- Base spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n+- Package root: `agentcube/`\n+- Source location: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Spec: AR-027 ŌĆö SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Overview\n\n<!-- Brief description of what this spec covers -->\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-027\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: <!-- Reference to base spec(s), e.g., sdk-python/spec.md -->\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\n<!-- Context and motivation for this change -->\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: <!-- Feature name -->\n\nThe system SHALL <!-- description -->\n\n#### Scenario: <!-- Scenario name -->\n- **GIVEN** <!-- precondition -->\n- **WHEN** <!-- trigger -->\n- **THEN** <!-- expected outcome -->\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. <!-- First acceptance criterion -->\n2. <!-- Second acceptance criterion -->\n3. <!-- Additional criteria as needed -->\n\n---\n\n**End of Delta Spec AR-027**","after":"# Delta Spec: AR-027 ŌĆö SDK CodeInterpreterClient\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the `CodeInterpreterClient` in the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). The client provides functionality to create Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and execute code/files via the Router (data plane).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-027\n- **Module**: `sdk-python`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Base Specs**: `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK requires a `CodeInterpreterClient` class that allows users to:\n1. Create and manage Code Interpreter sessions through the Workload Manager (control plane)\n2. Execute commands, run code, and manage files through the Router (data plane)\n3. Handle session lifecycle including context manager support and proper cleanup\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### AR-027-001: CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL construct a client that either reuses `session_id` or creates a session via `ControlPlaneClient.create_session`, then initializes `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` with header `x-agentcube-session-id`.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-001-A ŌĆö Context manager cleanup\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n- **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n- **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`, which closes the data-plane session, deletes the control-plane session if `session_id` was set, and closes the control plane HTTP session\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-001-B ŌĆö Data plane init failure after session create\n- **GIVEN** `session_id` was not provided and `create_session` succeeded\n- **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises\n- **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning, call `delete_session(session_id)`, set `session_id` to `None`, and re-raise\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-001-C ŌĆö Router URL required\n- **GIVEN** neither `router_url` nor environment variable `ROUTER_URL` is set\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterClient.__init__` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` explaining that Router URL must be provided via argument or `ROUTER_URL`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-001-D ŌĆö Constructor parameters with defaults\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with default parameters\n- **WHEN** the constructor runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL set `name=\"my-interpreter\"`, `namespace=\"default\"`, `ttl=3600`, `verbose=False`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-001-E ŌĆö Reuse existing session_id\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is instantiated with an existing `session_id`\n- **WHEN** initialization runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL skip session creation and use the provided session_id directly for data plane initialization\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-002: Code Interpreter operations ŌĆö execute, files, stop\n\nThe system SHALL expose `execute_command`, `run_code`, `write_file`, `upload_file`, `download_file`, `list_files`, and `stop` delegating to the data plane client where applicable.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-A ŌĆö Command non-zero exit\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command` receives a response with `exit_code != 0`\n- **WHEN** the response JSON is parsed\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-B ŌĆö Python code execution path\n- **GIVEN** `language` is `python`, `py`, or `python3`\n- **WHEN** `run_code` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL write a timestamped `.py` file via `write_file` and execute `python3 <file>` through `execute_command`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-C ŌĆö Write file operation\n- **GIVEN** `write_file(content, remote_path)` is called\n- **WHEN** the request succeeds\n- **THEN** the file SHALL be created at the specified remote path with content base64 encoded and mode `0644`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-D ŌĆö Upload file operation\n- **GIVEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` is called\n- **WHEN** the file exists locally\n- **THEN** the file SHALL be uploaded as multipart form data to `api/files` with the session header\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-E ŌĆö Download file operation\n- **GIVEN** `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` is called\n- **WHEN** the remote file exists\n- **THEN** the file SHALL be downloaded as a stream and written to the local path\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-F ŌĆö List files operation\n- **GIVEN** `list_files(path=\".\")` is called\n- **WHEN** the request succeeds\n- **THEN** the system SHALL return the listing from `api/files` with query parameter `path`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-002-G ŌĆö Stop operation\n- **GIVEN** `stop()` is called\n- **WHEN** the client has an active session\n- **THEN** the data plane session SHALL be closed and the control plane session SHALL be deleted\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-003: HTTP client contracts ŌĆö control plane\n\nThe system SHALL use `requests.Session` with connection pooling (`HTTPAdapter`) for Workload Manager calls.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-003-A ŌĆö Create session\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient.create_session(name, namespace, metadata=None, ttl=3600)`\n- **WHEN** the request succeeds\n- **THEN** the client SHALL `POST {base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` with JSON body `{\"name\",\"namespace\",\"ttl\",\"metadata\"}` and return `data[\"sessionId\"]` or raise `ValueError` if absent\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-003-B ŌĆö Delete session\n- **GIVEN** `delete_session(session_id)`\n- **WHEN** the server returns 404\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`; on other failures it SHALL log and return `False`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-003-C ŌĆö Workload Manager URL and auth\n- **GIVEN** `workload_manager_url` and `auth_token` may be omitted\n- **WHEN** the client initializes\n- **THEN** `base_url` SHALL resolve from `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; token SHALL resolve from `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` via `read_token_from_file`, and if present set `Authorization: Bearer {token}`\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-004: HTTP client contracts ŌĆö data plane (Code Interpreter)\n\nThe system SHALL target Router-relative paths under `{base_url}` derived from `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{ns}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` unless `base_url` is passed explicitly.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-004-A ŌĆö Data plane base URL construction\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed with `router_url`, `namespace`, and `cr_name`\n- **WHEN** `base_url` is not provided\n- **THEN** the base URL SHALL be constructed as `urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-004-B ŌĆö Execute command\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` posts to `api/execute`\n- **THEN** the body SHALL be JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` and read timeout SHALL be `timeout_value + 2.0` seconds when numeric (to avoid `ReadTimeout` before PicoD returns exit 124)\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-004-C ŌĆö Write file via data plane\n- **WHEN** `write_file` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST api/files` with base64 `content`, `path`, `mode` `\"0644\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-004-D ŌĆö Upload file via data plane\n- **WHEN** `upload_file` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL `POST` multipart to `api/files` with headers including `x-agentcube-session-id`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-004-E ŌĆö Download file via data plane\n- **WHEN** `download_file` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL `GET api/files/{clean_path}` with `stream=True` where `clean_path = remote_path.lstrip(\"/\")`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-004-F ŌĆö List files via data plane\n- **WHEN** `list_files` runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL `GET api/files` with query parameter `path`\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-005: Session header management\n\nThe system SHALL use lowercase header name `x-agentcube-session-id` for SDK Router requests.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-005-A ŌĆö Code Interpreter session header\n- **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n- **WHEN** any `_request` or upload runs\n- **THEN** the session SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}` (upload sets it explicitly on the multipart POST)\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-006: Exception hierarchy\n\nThe system SHALL define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, and `DataPlaneError` in `agentcube.exceptions`.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-006-A ŌĆö Command failure\n- **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n- **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n- **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (subclass of `AgentCubeError`)\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-006-B ŌĆö Session error definition\n- **GIVEN** `SessionError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n- **WHEN** a session operation fails\n- **THEN** `SessionError` MAY be raised by the client\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-006-C ŌĆö Data plane error definition\n- **GIVEN** `DataPlaneError` is defined in `agentcube.exceptions`\n- **WHEN** a data plane operation fails\n- **THEN** `DataPlaneError` MAY be raised by the client\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-007: Timeout behavior\n\nThe system SHALL default control-plane and data-plane read timeouts to `120` seconds and connect timeout to `5.0` seconds unless overridden per call.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-007-A ŌĆö Per-call override for code execution\n- **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n- **WHEN** `timeout` is `None`\n- **THEN** the effective timeout value SHALL default to `self.timeout` (`120`) for constructing the PicoD timeout string and read-timeout buffer logic\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-007-B ŌĆö Connection pool configuration\n- **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` or `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` is constructed\n- **WHEN** no pool settings are provided\n- **THEN** the defaults SHALL be `pool_connections=10` and `pool_maxsize=10`\n\n---\n\n### AR-027-008: Public API surface\n\nThe system SHALL export the `CodeInterpreterClient` from the root package.\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-008-A ŌĆö Root package exports\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/__init__.py` is imported\n- **WHEN** `__all__` is accessed\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: AR-027-008-B ŌĆö Clients submodule exports\n- **GIVEN** `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` is imported\n- **WHEN** `__all__` is accessed\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain `[\"ControlPlaneClient\", \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\", \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"]`\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC001: CodeInterpreterClient constructs with proper defaults (name, namespace, ttl, verbose)\n- [ ] AC002: CodeInterpreterClient creates session via ControlPlaneClient when session_id not provided\n- [ ] AC003: CodeInterpreterClient supports context manager protocol with proper cleanup\n- [ ] AC004: CodeInterpreterClient handles data plane init failure with session cleanup\n- [ ] AC005: CodeInterpreterClient raises ValueError when router_url is missing\n- [ ] AC006: execute_command raises CommandExecutionError on non-zero exit code\n- [ ] AC007: run_code supports python/py/python3 languages with timestamped file execution\n- [ ] AC008: write_file creates remote files with base64 content and mode 0644\n- [ ] AC009: upload_file uploads files via multipart to data plane\n- [ ] AC010: download_file downloads files as streams to local path\n- [ ] AC011: list_files returns file listing from data plane\n- [ ] AC012: stop closes data plane and deletes control plane session\n- [ ] AC013: ControlPlaneClient.create_session returns sessionId from response\n- [ ] AC014: ControlPlaneClient.delete_session returns True on 404\n- [ ] AC015: ControlPlaneClient resolves base_url and auth from env/args\n- [ ] AC016: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient constructs base_url from router components\n- [ ] AC017: Session header x-agentcube-session-id is set on all data plane requests\n- [ ] AC018: Exception hierarchy includes AgentCubeError, CommandExecutionError, SessionError, DataPlaneError\n- [ ] AC019: Default timeouts are 120s read, 5.0s connect\n- [ ] AC020: Connection pool defaults are 10 connections, 10 max size\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Notes\n\n### Package Layout\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pyproject.toml` | Package `agentcube-sdk`, dependencies |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports |\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` |\n\n### Key Components\n\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | Main client for Code Interpreter sessions |\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | Handles Workload Manager API calls |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | Handles Router data plane API calls |\n| `AgentCubeError` | Base exception class |\n| `CommandExecutionError` | Raised on command non-zero exit |\n| `SessionError` | Raised on session operations failure |\n| `DataPlaneError` | Raised on data plane operations failure |\n\n### Configuration Resolution\n\n| Component | Resolved settings |\n|-----------|-------------------|\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `base_url` ŌåÉ `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`; `Authorization` ŌåÉ `auth_token` or SA token file; `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n| `CodeInterpreterClient` | `router_url` ŌåÉ arg or `ROUTER_URL` (required); `workload_manager_url` / `auth_token` passed to `ControlPlaneClient` |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0`, `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10`; `base_url` from `base_url` **or** `router_url`+`namespace`+`cr_name` |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Base design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n- Base spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n- Package root: `agentcube/`\n- Source location: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/sdk-python/`","additions":253,"deletions":13},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-027/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775867551970,"end":1775867552006}}}}
